annotationA: CDK7/cyclin H assembly factor MAT1; RNA polymerase II carboxy-terminal domain kinase activity; zinc ion binding; core RNA polymerase binding transcription factor activity; cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: cell cycle; transcription initiation from RNA polymerase II promoter
annotationB: RE12958p; Dacapo (Dap) is a Cyclin-dependent kinase inhibitor in the CIP/KIP family. It binds to CycE-Cdk2 complexes and thereby inhibits their protein kinase activity. Upregulation of Dap is required after the last mitosis for arresting cells in G1/G0 before terminal differentiation in many post-mitotic cell types
